    <h3>What is Yoga? </h3>
<p>Yoga is a practice that originated in ancient India and is a combination of physical, mental, and spiritual elements. It consists of a series of postures (asanas) and breathing exercises (pranayama) that promote physical strength, flexibility, and relaxation. Yoga is also an effective meditation practice that helps calm the mind and reduce stress and anxiety. </p><br>

<h3>What is Meditation? </h3>
<p>Meditation is a practice that involves training the mind to focus on a single object, thought, or activity. It can help reduce stress and anxiety, improve concentration and focus, and increase self-awareness. There are different types of meditation practices such as mindfulness meditation, loving-kindness meditation, and transcendental meditation which can be done in various positions such as sitting, standing, walking or lying down. </p>
    
    <ol>
        <li><b>Tadasana (Mountain Pose):</b> Stand tall with your feet together. Stretch your arms upward and breathe deeply.</li>
        <li><b>Vrikshasana (Tree Pose):</b> Balance on one leg, placing the other foot on your inner thigh. Raise your arms upward or keep them in prayer position.</li>
        <li><b>Virabhadrasana I (Warrior I):</b> Step one leg forward, bending the knee, and raise your arms overhead while stretching the back leg.</li>
        <li><b>Trikonasana (Triangle Pose):</b> Stand with feet wide apart, stretch your arms to the sides, and bend sideways to touch your ankle.</li>
        <li><b>Bhujangasana (Cobra Pose):</b> Lie on your stomach, place your hands beneath your shoulders, and lift your chest as you inhale.</li>
    </ol>
    
